text: Magnistipula conrauana is a species of plant in the family Chrysobalanaceae. It is endemic to Cameroon. Its natural habitats are subtropical or tropical moist lowland forests and subtropical or tropical moist montane forests. It is threatened by habitat loss. ==References== Category:Chrysobalanaceae Category:Endemic flora of Cameroon Category:Endangered plants Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot
